<h1>Case 6 — Emergency Coordination Tower</h1>

<h2>Brief Description</h2>
<p>
The Emergency Coordination Tower acts as Velora’s central hub for managing disaster and emergency services 
including fire response, medical emergencies, police assistance, and rescue teams. 
It ensures rapid decision-making and optimal deployment of emergency units.
</p>

<h2>Rising Problems</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Difficulty in identifying which emergency unit is closest to the incident location.</li>
    <li>Multiple emergencies occurring at the same time causing response delays.</li>
    <li>Lack of communication between fire, police, and medical departments.</li>
    <li>Slow dispatch due to manual decision-making.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Solutions / Logic Used</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Priority Queue (Heap):</strong> Rank incoming emergencies based on severity.</li>
    <li><strong>Hash Table:</strong> Track availability and status of rescue units (ambulance, police, fire).</li>
    <li><strong>Dijkstra’s Algorithm:</strong> Determine the fastest route for the nearest emergency unit.</li>
    <li><strong>Queue:</strong> Manage multi-step rescue workflows and dispatch sequences.</li>
    <li><strong>BFS:</strong> Used for scanning nearby backup units or alternate routes.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Suitable SDGs</h2>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 3 — Good Health & Well-Being</strong>
    <p>Supports immediate medical care and reduces response time during health emergencies.</p>
</div>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 11 — Sustainable Cities & Communities</strong>
    <p>Enhances preparedness and resilience during accidents, fires, and natural disasters.</p>
</div>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 9 — Industry, Innovation & Infrastructure</strong>
    <p>Uses smart analytics and intelligent routing to modernize emergency infrastructure.</p>
</div>

